      "contents": "<div class=\"markitup-box\">\n\t\t\tThe Transportation Security Administration (TSA) limits lithium-ion batteries to 100 watt hours (Wh) per battery when packed in carry-on baggage. With airline approval, you can bring two larger spare batteries up to 160 Wh. Batteries with ratings of up to 27,000mAh are allowed on planes. You can bring a portable charger on a plane if it is packed securely in your carry-on luggage, but you cannot pack chargers in check-in luggage.<br/>\n美国对于充电宝也有容量要求的，100Wh以下能带上飞机，和国内标准一样。\t\t</div>",
      "date": "2024-04-08",
      "agree_count": 7,
      "discussion_count": 0,
      "discussions": []
    },
